<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-05-27T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-05-27T16:00:00-05:00" n="59" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89France/310b: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-05-27T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 27,
                                        1926—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>146. According to the Secretary of the Treasury the possible date now
                            mentioned for Congress to adjourn is June 19. He points out that if
                            Congress is to take favorable action before adjournment early approval
                            by French Parliament is important.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
